          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a kind of early Hindu philosophical treatise that examines the nature of existence through aphorisms, the Great sayings (mahāvakyas), by means of the use of mantras. This collection is likely a medieval work, edited by followers of Advaita Vedānta, for the purpose of providing an overview or essence of that school of philosophy.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Mahāvākyopaniṣad</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: itī māhāṃvākyopaniṣatsamāptā // (f. 2v).</colophon>
